@startuml
title DNS Spoofing - Conceptual Flow

actor User
participant "User Device" as Client
participant "DNS Resolver" as DNS
participant "Attacker" as A
participant "Fake Website" as Fake

User -> Client: Enter legitimate website address

Client -> DNS: Send DNS query for domain
A --> Client: Send forged DNS reply first

Client -> Client: Cache / accept fake IP address

Client -> Fake: Connect to malicious server
Fake --> Client: Return fake webpage
Client --> User: Show fake website

note over Client
If the forged DNS response
is accepted, the user is sent
to the wrong destination
end note

note over A
Attacker spoofs the DNS reply
without changing what the user typed
end note

@enduml